  "id": "s14amazonas",
  "stac_version": "1.1.0",
  "description": "The Sentinel-1 for Science Amazonas project demonstrates the use of Sentinel-1 SAR data to monitor deforestation in the Amazon basin. It employs a space-time data cube design (StatCubes) and AI with a U-net architecture to detect forest loss, processing over 450 TB of data from 2015 to 2021. The project developed user-friendly tools to access and process data, created dynamic deforestation maps, and aims to integrate carbon mapping using NFI, ESA CCI, and GEDI products.",
